						<summary>

						<p>This is a damaged fragment of an inscription of Sundarapāṇḍya who presented the Chōḷa country. It seems to record some endowment made by Śīvallavaṉ Tirunīlakaṇṭaṉ Toṇḍaimān mentioned in No. 445 above for offerings to god Vaṇḍuvarāpatippiḷḷai (Kṛishṇa ?) and the goddess (Pirāṭṭiyār) in the Naḍuviltirumuṟṟam at Arikēsarinallūr. </p>						

						</summary>
